Markdown is a style of editing plain text in a way that tells the computer what you want it to do. For example, wrapping a word in asterisks (*) will tell the computer you want that word italicized. There's more info at <a href="http://howtomarkdown.com">howtomarkdown.com</a>. Don't forget single line breaks are tricky... you need to end the previous line with two (or more) spaces.